Game Rules:

1. If the goat and the hay are left on the same side of the river without the man, the goat will eat the hay.

2. If the wolf and the goat are left on the same side of the river without the man, the wolf will eat the goat.

3. In order to win, you must move all the objects across the river without any being eaten.

How to Play:

1. To move an object (man, wolf, goat, or hay) on/off the boat, write the name of the object for [move object] and type enter. Then, type “onto boat” or “off of boat” for [move to].

2. To move the boat to the other side, write “boat” for [move object], and write “right” or “left” for [move to]